<subSubSection id="C34288BD1E13FFAEFF0BA230FACED941" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFF0BA230FD17DC4D" blockId="12.[145,762,1545,1628]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFF0BA230FE5FDC0F" authority="Warren, 1909" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1909" box="[145,434,1545,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Plateoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFF0BA230FEE8DC0F" box="[145,261,1545,1566]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Plateoplia</emphasis>
Warren, 1909
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="54E365941E13FFAEFE5BA233FE15DC0E" box="[449,504,1546,1567]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFDFDA230FE57DC2C" authority="Warren, 1901" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Tephrinopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochriciliata">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFDFDA230FEFEDC2C" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Tephrinopsis ochriciliata</emphasis>
Warren, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFD20A211FDEFDC4D" authority="Wallengren, 1875" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1875" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Tephrina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrobelia">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFD20A211FEDCDC4A" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Tephrina acrobelia</emphasis>
Wallengren, 1875
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F34F9BA61E13FFAEFD96A27FFD8DDC4D" box="[524,608,1606,1628]" name="Angola" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Angola</collectingCountry>
: Cubal River.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFF0BA24CFEFBDC9D" blockId="12.[145,278,1653,1676]" box="[145,278,1653,1676]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFF0BA24CFEFBDC9D" box="[145,278,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFF0BA29DFEA8DCC9" blockId="12.[145,761,1700,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFF0BA29DFF23DCA8" box="[145,206,1700,1721]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Head</emphasis>
. Chaetosemata extended. Antenna fasciculate, not bipectinate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFF0BA2C8FDE1DD34" blockId="12.[145,761,1776,1829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFF0BA2C8FF38DD17" box="[145,213,1777,1798]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Wings</emphasis>
(Fig. 3). Rounded, ochreous with terminal, postmedial, and submedial lines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFF0BA304FB33DB09" blockId="12.[145,761,1853,1906]" lastBlockId="12.[809,1425,197,280]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFF0BA304FED8DD43" box="[145,309,1853,1874]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1363C7B31E13FFAEFED9A304FE79DD42" box="[323,404,1853,1875]" captionStart="Figures 68–71" captionStartId="13.[159,249,1375,1396]" captionTargetBox="[161,1399,196,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-202@13.[161,1441,196,1345]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 68–71. Plateoplia acrobelia: 68, ♂ genitalia; 69, sternum A8 of ♂; 70, ♀ genitalia, ostium region; 71, ♀ genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434174/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Uncus triangular, large, with spine-like setae. Gnathos prominent with large, triangular medial element. Valva: almost completely divided; costa with spine-like setae; sacculus with digitate process. Saccus long, pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A509FB61DB74" blockId="12.[809,1424,304,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A509FB97DB54" box="[809,1146,304,326]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Pregenital abdomen of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1363C7B31E13FFAEFB0AA509FB05DB57" box="[1168,1256,304,326]" captionStart="Figures 68–71" captionStartId="13.[159,249,1375,1396]" captionTargetBox="[161,1399,196,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-202@13.[161,1441,196,1345]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 68–71. Plateoplia acrobelia: 68, ♂ genitalia; 69, sternum A8 of ♂; 70, ♀ genitalia, ostium region; 71, ♀ genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434174/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Sternum A8 weakly modified along margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A544FBBDDBFE" blockId="12.[809,1425,381,495]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A544FC15DB83" box="[809,1016,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1363C7B31E13FFAEFB8DA544FB55DB82" box="[1047,1208,381,403]" captionStart="Figures 68–71" captionStartId="13.[159,249,1375,1396]" captionTargetBox="[161,1399,196,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-202@13.[161,1441,196,1345]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 68–71. Plateoplia acrobelia: 68, ♂ genitalia; 69, sternum A8 of ♂; 70, ♀ genitalia, ostium region; 71, ♀ genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434174/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Figs 70, 71</figureCitation>
). Ostium bursae: sterigma complex. Corpus bursae small, elongated, not round, without spines, and with a small signum with a single small tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A631FBBDD868" blockId="12.[809,1425,519,633]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A631FC74D80C" box="[809,921,520,541]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The shape of the valva is distinctive. The corpus bursae has a signum and lacks spines, unlike the densely spinose condition in 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFB21A67DFAD9D848" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1900" box="[1211,1332,580,601]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Platypepla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFB21A67DFAD9D848" box="[1211,1332,580,601]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Platypepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in many species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFC7CA65AFBA4D869" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1904" box="[998,1097,611,632]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Milocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFC7CA65AFBA4D869" box="[998,1097,611,632]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Milocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A6A8FB18D8B6" blockId="12.[809,1269,657,679]" box="[809,1269,657,679]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A6A8FC59D8B7" box="[809,948,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Distribution</emphasis>
. Southern and East Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A686FB08D8C4" blockId="12.[809,1253,703,725]" box="[809,1253,703,725]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A686FC45D8C5" box="[809,936,703,724]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Foodplants</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFC21A6F9FBBFD8C4" box="[955,1106,704,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ximeniaceae" genus="Ximenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFC21A6F9FBF6D8C4" box="[955,1051,704,725]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Ximenia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFBF8A686FB34D8C4" box="[1122,1241,703,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Olacaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Olacaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A6D7FC08D930" blockId="12.[809,1425,749,802]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A6D7FC4CD912" box="[809,929,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFC2EA6D4FBC5D913" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1909" box="[948,1064,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Plateoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFC2EA6D4FBC5D913" box="[948,1064,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Plateoplia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A0B51E13FFAEFA95A6D4FA65D913" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1900" box="[1295,1416,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Platypepla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFA95A6D4FA65D913" box="[1295,1416,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Platypepla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group of genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE7DB361E13FFAEFCB3A703FACED941" blockId="12.[809,1315,826,848]" box="[809,1315,826,848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis id="B92C07241E13FFAEFCB3A703FC1AD95E" box="[809,1015,826,847]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="269">Number of species</emphasis>
. The genus is monotypic.
</paragraph>
